🚨How to reuse your Happy Planner monthly tabs!

I know a lot of you reuse your planners from year to year, but I know that monthly tab is tricky because it has the back of a calendar on it.

Check out this video to see how I got around that.

A couple of genius teachers told me that they actually buy old Happy Planners when they’re like 90% off. They then combine those parts and things from my planner add ons to create their planner. So smart! 💡 

Want to pause this video? Just press down and it will pause for you! 

PS I decided to laminate the checklist so it can be reused each week. Just write on it with wet erase marker and wipe it down the following week. 

I’m linking my planner add ons in my profile for you - http://bit.ly/plannerbasics

Flashback Friday to the day our class fairy joined us five years ago ✨🧚🏻‍♀️✨

I always used these notes from @teachcreatemotivate. They’re in her shop as a freebie!! The door is from Amazon. This exact one is gone but I linked a similar one in my Amazon Highlights if you’re looking into picking one up!

I also liked to leave a little treat. I’ve done different things. Mini erasers and pixie sticks were the most popular with my kids!

Swipe over to see the “real” desk fairy checking out some desks. 🤭 

Several teachers requested the quote seen here next to the door. I put one in my shop that you can cut out with your Cricut or on paper. Link in bio- https://bit.ly/thedeskfairy

🚨How to reuse your Happy Planner monthly tabs!

I know a lot of you reuse your planners from year to year, but I know that monthly tab is tricky because it has the back of a calendar on it.

Check out this video to see how I got around that.

A couple of genius teachers told me that they actually buy old Happy Planners when they’re like 90% off. They then combine those parts and things from my planner add ons to create their planner. So smart! 💡 

Want to pause this video? Just press down and it will pause for you! 

PS I decided to laminate the checklist so it can be reused each week. Just write on it with wet erase marker and wipe it down the following week. 

I’m linking my planner add ons in my profile for you - http://bit.ly/plannerbasics
